  "body": "### Description\n\nGoogle tokens don't have claims identifying a user name set which `JsonWebToken.getName()` (and indirectly, `SecurityIdentity.getPrincipal().getName()`) use, it would have standatd claims like `name` set but not `preferred_username` or MP JWT specific `upn` which MP JWT spec talks specifies. \r\n`sub` is only claim that Google sets which also MP JWT refers to as the last fallback. But it is not usable as a user name value, it is a unique user identifier like `123....9` or similar. `JsonWebToken` has a `getSubject` if the subject value is required.\r\n\r\nSo the `google` provider has to be configured with a `name` claim as a preferred principal name.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
